GEE WIZ rushed to the gain command into the first turn and drew off into the backstretch, set the pace into the stretch and weakened. MOON SCAMPER raced five-wide on the backstretch in the middle of the pack and gave way on the second turn. EL COVER pressed the pace for three furlongs, bid for the lead and bore out tiring on the second turn.

EL REY'S REINA ducked out at the start bumping HIDDEN INTENTIONS and pinching her back, angled out three-wide on the backstretch to press the pace to the second turn and tired. LEMONSINA was bumped at the start, raced five-wide on the backstretch and posed no threat.
